This version of json-stream-es is downloaded from the tip of this commit: https://github.com/cdauth/json-stream-es/commit/087b6331573e49e895da5c0ef96d29d26409776a

The following changes have been made to it:
- Removed tests
- Removed unnecesary bundler / TS config / eslint files
- Resolved sloppy imports (added ".ts" to every import, at the end)
- Resolved a bug that prevented the use of the advanced splitters outside of Node.js (abuse of Object.create() -- also was there a reason to use it?)
- Dropped Node engine restriction
